# infra/k8s — production Helm charts for `<project-name>`

Production **Kubernetes** deployment for the `event-driven-eu` backend, shipped as
Forge **Helm values overlays** on upstream charts (the B.8.7 Zitadel /
B.8.4 Envoy chart-referenced-hybrid convention — upstream chart + `values-forge.yaml`
overlay + docs; no vendored `Chart.yaml`).

> **Production, not dev.** The everyday local loop is `docker-compose.dev.yml`
> (`task dev:up`: single-node NATS + Postgres) and the optional
> `infra/temporal/docker-compose.temporal.yml` dev server. Those are dev-scoped.
> **This directory is what you deploy to an EU K8s cluster.**

| Chart | What | Doc |
|-------|------|-----|
| `temporal-cluster/` | Temporal server cluster (history/matching/frontend/worker) on a Postgres-backed store | [`temporal-cluster/README.md`](temporal-cluster/README.md) |
| `nats-jetstream/` | 3-node clustered NATS + JetStream (RAFT, file-store PVCs) — the event backbone | [`nats-jetstream/README.md`](nats-jetstream/README.md) |

Each chart carries its own **T1 / T2 / T3** self-host EU compliance posture
(citing `.forge/standards/global/compliance-tiers.md`). Both self-host cleanly on
EU K8s for **T2** and on SecNumCloud-qualified EU clusters for **T3** — no
US-jurisdiction SaaS dependency. See [`docs/COMPLIANCE.md`](../../../../../../docs/COMPLIANCE.md)
for tier selection (declare yours in `.forge/.forge-tier`).

The Postgres event store the backend uses (`infra/postgres/`) is deployed
separately; production Temporal SHOULD use a **dedicated** Postgres instance for
its `temporal` + `temporal_visibility` databases (see `temporal-cluster/README.md`).
